DIAGNOSIS: Males and females of 

O. microfoliata

have pale spots on the labium (
Figs. 509, 515
) and the sternum mottled with dark spots forming an irregular wide band along the margin. Males are further recognized by the small prolateral swelling at the base of tibia I (
Fig. 511
) and the reniform palpal tibia (
Fig. 516
). Females have genitalia with AUS tube shaped as in 

O. clavigera

,from which the females cannot be separated (see note in 

O. clavigera

).
